This tutorial will use R and python3 environments available through anaconda.

In order to keep eveything contained we'll use anaconda's environment feature.

This tutorial may be completed on a local machine or on the olympus compute cluster.

1.) Clone the git repository to your local machine or to the olympus cluster

git clone git@github.com:PSC-PublicHealth/midas-mission-parallel.git
cd midas-mission-parallel

2.) Create your anaconda environment, install all dependencies and activate the environment

conda env create -f mission-env.yml -n mission
source activate mission

ALTERNATIVE (Olympus only):

ml load anaconda/4.3.1
ml load envs
source activate conda.python3.mission

3.) Unzip the example data

unzip dat.zip
